				\begin{document}$${\log}_2\left( {\frac{{{\mathrm{treatment}}\left( {\frac{{M + X}}{M}} \right)}}{{{\mathrm{control}}\left( {\frac{{M + X}}{M}} \right)}}} \right)$$\end{document}where M is the area under the curve measured by LC–MS of molecules made up of 12C atoms only, and M + X is the area under the curve measured by LC–MS of molecules with 13C-isotope atoms incorporated into the molecule, X being the number of 13C-isotope atoms incorporated. When multiple biological replicates were available, they were averaged before dividing treatment by control. The untreated control replicates shown are a single representative replicate normalized to the average of all replicates, which helps visualize any variation between controls.

